data.description: This custom built ranch style home is nestled in the majestic Colorado Rocky Mountains! This 2,988 s/f home offers 3 bedroom, 3 bath, main level living with a partially finished basement with a large family room, 3/4 bath, storage rooms and pantry. The main level has 1,494 total living s/f, and the basement has 787 total living s/f, for a total of 2,291 total living space with an additional 697 s/f of storage space and a pantry. The detached oversized 2 car garage has an attached storage area and workshop area for those who enjoy working on their cars, trucks and recreational vehicles. This home sports 1.74 acres, corner lot and one of the larger lots in the subdivision. For those green thumbs who want to grow their own vegetables, the seller built a greenhouse located on the eastern side of the house. This home offers gorgeous views of the mountains. While gazing at the stars from the front or back decks, one feels as if they can reach out and touch them. The nightly sightings of falling stars give us a peak into the heavens, and the morning sunrise warms and melts the morning dew clearing the way for a midday snack for the dear, elk and other wildlife. Recreational opportunities such as hiking, fishing, skiing, hunting, ATVing, horseback riding and wildlife photography are just minutes from this home. This quintessential Colorado mountain home is located near Florissant Fossil Beds, Florissant, Cripple Creek, Divide, Woodland Park, Charis Bible College and is minutes from the big city of Colorado Springs. Some of our nations favorite parks such as Pikes Peak, Dome Rock, 11 Mile Reservoir, Spinney Reservoir and Tarryall are all within minutes of this home. If you love the mountains, fresh air, big beautiful blue skies and recreational opportunities beyond your wildest dreams, this home is for you!
